Scope of the Reference Implementation

This release includes:

structural state definitions
rule-based resolution logic
a minimal executable reference (tiny kernel)
outputs and reference traces

SLANG-Money defines a deterministic structural model where financial state emerges from structure:

resolve(structure) ->
    state_visible (full)    if complete and consistent
    state_visible (partial) if partially satisfied
    no_visible_state        if conflicting

What This Demonstrates

• financial state without transactions
• independence from settlement and execution pipelines
• independence from ordering and synchronization
• structural maturity governing visibility
• safe handling of incomplete or conflicting structure
• deterministic and reproducible outcomes

Conformance

An implementation is considered compatible if it preserves:

structure-based correctness
independence from transactions as a requirement
deterministic resolution
structural maturity-driven visibility
reproducibility under equivalent inputs
explicit handling of incomplete and conflicting structure

Conformance is judged by observable behavior, not internal implementation.

Relationship to Shunyaya Framework

SLANG-Money is part of the broader Shunyaya framework.

It builds on:

SLANG → structural resolution without execution
STOCRS → structure-first computation (correctness from structure)
STIME → Structural Time (time from valid structural transitions)
SSUM-Time → structural time reconstruction engine
ORL → structural correctness across systems

